    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>CRUSE*</h1><p>Small earthen vessel or flask, about four to six inches (10 to15 centimeters) tall, used for holding liquids (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:12-1Kgs17:16\">1&nbsp;Kgs 17:12–16</a>). In the kjv, two other Hebrew words are translated “cruse.” However, a bottle or jar is probably in view in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:3\">1&nbsp;Kings 14:3</a>, and an open dish or bowl in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:20\">2&nbsp;Kings 2:20</a>.</p><p><em>See also</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"6963\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Pottery</span>.</p>",
